When you have even numbers, you don't lose anything by going NT. If you have odd numbers, you lose a miskill. So, today we are 7-3 and we have two swings to get a Wolf before we lose (if we were wrong both times), because if we go wrong today, it would be 5-3 tomorrow (presuming night kills go through), and then 3-3 and game over after D4's execution. If we NT, we don't lose one of those swings, because it would be 6-3 tomorrow, we can swing and go to 4-3 and still have that second swing. If we were on an odd number player count, say 11 alive, we would have three swings (8-3, 6-3, 4-3) and so NT would be giving up a free shot at the Wolves.
Makes sense

So unless you're in a block/protection/night kill heavy game, you should pretty much always execute if there are an odd number of players alive.
